President Obama has nominated Judge Patty Shwartz for the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit. He praises her long and impressive record of service and fair decision-making. Judge Shwartz has been a Magistrate Judge in the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey since 2003 and has also been an adjunct professor of law at Fordham University School of Law since 2009. She has a strong background in law, having received her B.A. from Rutgers University and her J.D. from the University of Pennsylvania Law School. She has worked as an associate at Pepper, Hamilton & Scheetz and served as a law clerk to the Honorable Harold A. Ackerman of the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey. She also has experience in the United States Attorney's Office for the District of New Jersey, where she held various leadership positions. As a Magistrate Judge, Judge Shwartz has handled numerous civil and criminal cases, issuing opinions and orders, writing reports and recommendations, conducting preliminary proceedings, and presiding over trials.